{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, while DL models have achieved remarkable success at specieslevel classification, differentiating between closely related taxa at taxonomic levels above the species, and across a broader range of clades, remains a persistent challenge.",
    "Addressing these limitations will necessitate continued innovation, particularly in the integration of domain-specific knowledge and the refinement of augmentation strategies.",
    "The expanding body of research in this area highlights the need to overcome these obstacles to further enhance the capabilities of fossil classification models.",
    "The field of fossil segmentation has seen significant advancements, driven by the introduction of DL techniques, particularly FCNs and U-Net architectures.",
    "Unlike classification tasks, segmentation poses greater challenges due to the need for pixel-wise accuracy, which is complicated by the effects of fossilization, such as erosion, disarticulation and fragmenta- tion."
  ]
}